│ This is an interesting bug. The root cause analysis is spot on. The `ipsccp` pass, when │
│ specializing functions, fails to reset its per-function reachability state. This leads  │
│ to an incorrect determination of dead blocks in a subsequent function analysis, causing │
│ an assertion when attempting to delete a block that is, in fact, still reachable.       │
│                                                                                         │
│ The fix is to clear the `LiveBlocks` set at the beginning of each function's analysis   │
│ within the main `runIPSCCP` loop. This ensures that the reachability information is     │
│ fresh for every function processed.                                                     │
│                                                                                         │
│ I will now apply this fix.                                                              │
│                                                                                         │
│ <tool_call>                                                                             │
│ {                                                                                       │
